  "prompt": "What is the best military school for troubled teens?",
  "response": "There are several reputable military-style schools and programs for troubled teens, but the best choice depends on the specific needs of the individual. Some well-known options include:\n\n1. Marine Military Academy (Harlingen, Texas)\n- Focuses on discipline and academic improvement\n- Serves boys ages 8-17\n\n2. Boys Ranch (Florida)\n- Provides therapeutic and educational support\n- Offers structured environment with counseling\n\n3. Gateway Academy (Las Vegas, Nevada)\n- Specializes in helping teens with behavioral and academic challenges\n- Provides therapeutic and educational support\n\n4. New Life Academy (Colorado)\n- Offers structure, discipline, and counseling\n- Helps teens develop leadership skills\n\nWhen choosing a program, consider:\n- The teen's specific behavioral issues\n- Academic needs\n- Cost of the program\n- Length of program\n- Therapeutic support\n- Accreditation\n\nIt's recommended to:\n- Consult with a professional counselor\n- Visit potential schools\n- Speak with program administrators\n- Get references and reviews\n- Involve the teen in the decision-making process\n\nEach teen is unique, so what works best will vary depending on individual circumstances.",
